 on a proper scale, compared to his pot, 

00:00:55.810 --> 00:00:58.450
 in pottery, it's going pretty well. 

00:00:58.450 --> 00:01:01.010
 On the other hand, he tends to push very hard, 

00:01:01.210 --> 00:01:04.210
 and to make between very long knots, and us, 

00:01:04.210 --> 00:01:07.250
 we want to avoid this, to branch the tree 

00:01:07.250 --> 00:01:09.020
 and try to give an appearance 

00:01:09.020 --> 00:01:12.020
 much more compact of this tree. 

00:01:12.020 --> 00:01:14.380
 So, simply, we're going to cut down the big stems, 

00:01:14.390 --> 00:01:17.390
 the between nodes too long. 

00:01:17.390 --> 00:01:19.390
 Everything that pushes up is eliminated, 

00:01:22.300 --> 00:01:25.360
 and everything that pushes down, we also eliminate. 

00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:28.820
 Always work in front of your tree, 

00:01:28.820 --> 00:01:30.820
 to see what we do. 

00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:33.880
 We're not going to look behind to cut a branch, 

00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:36.520
 we turn his tray, 

