 and so we turn his tree 

00:01:38.890 --> 00:01:41.890
 and we always have the silhouette of the tree. So you have to understand 

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:45.540
 we work on one side, the front, 

00:01:45.540 --> 00:01:48.620
 but that finally we must give volume to the tree and therefore, 

00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:54.680
 we will homogenize the work front and back. 

00:01:56.140 --> 00:02:00.160
 What we are trying to do too, is that the branches must be tapered. 

00:02:01.060 --> 00:02:04.920
 The appearance of the branch must be more and more fine and branched. 

00:02:04.920 --> 00:02:07.660
 In principle you do not tear any branch, 

00:02:07.660 --> 00:02:10.060
 even departures on the trunk, 

00:02:10.320 --> 00:02:13.240
 always prefer to cut with scissors. 

